  "prompt": "What is the best email subject line you have received from Snapdeal, Flipkart or Amazon or any other deal site?",
  "response": "The best email subject lines from deal sites like Snapdeal, Flipkart, Amazon, or others are typically those that are catchy, create a sense of urgency, and clearly communicate value or savings. Here are some examples that have stood out:\n\n1. **\"Ending Tonight: Save Extra 50% on Best-Selling Styles\"**  \n   - Creates urgency and highlights a significant discount.\n\n2. **\"Your Exclusive Deal: Up to 70% Off on Top Brands\"**  \n   - Personalizes the offer and emphasizes exclusivity and savings.\n\n3. **\"Flash Sale Alert: 3 Hours Only! Don\u2019t Miss Out\"**  \n   - Drives urgency with a clear time limit.\n\n4. **\"Hurry! Last Chance to Grab Your Favorites at 60% Off\"**  \n   - Combines urgency with the appeal of favorite items.\n\n5. **\"Deals You Can\u2019t Resist: Up to 80% Off | Shop Now\"**  \n   - Highlights irresistible savings and includes a clear call-to-action.\n\n6. **\"Unlock Premium Perks: Early Access to Sale + Extra 10% Off\"**  \n   - Appeals to exclusivity and additional benefits.\n\n7. **\"Back to School Blowout: Up to 75% Off on Essentials\"**  \n   - Tailored to a specific event and emphasizes relevance.\n\n8. **\"Your Wishlist Just Got Cheaper: Extra 30% Off\"**  \n   - Personalizes the offer and connects with the customer\u2019s interests.\n\n9. **\"Biggest Sale of the Year Starts Now \u2013 Save Big!\"**  \n   - Creates excitement and sets the tone for a major event.\n\n10. **\"Limited Stock Alert: Grab It Before It\u2019s Gone\"**  \n    - Focuses on scarcity and encourages immediate action.\n\nThe effectiveness of these subject lines lies in their ability to grab attention, evoke curiosity, and prompt immediate action. They often combine elements of urgency, exclusivity, and value to make the offer irresistible.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
